---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Evert Ramos|Terms">
  <div class="py-12 bg-gray-50 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Terms of Use</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            <strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2025
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            By using this website and making payments, you agree to these terms of use. 
            If you do not agree, please do not use our services.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. Nature of Payments</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Payments made through this platform may be for:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 mb-6">
            <li>Technical services rendered</li>
            <li>Support for open source projects</li>
            <li>Voluntary contributions</li>
          </ul>
          
          <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
            <p class="text-yellow-800 font-semibold">
              IMPORTANT: This payment does not create any obligation on our part to provide any service, 
              unless we have a signed contract with valid digital certificate.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">3. Payment Processing</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            All payments are processed by Stripe. We do not store credit card information. 
            You are responsible for providing accurate and valid payment information.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">4. Refunds and Administrative Fees</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Refunds are analyzed case by case. <strong>To request a refund, contact us 
            STRICTLY by email:</strong> <span id="email-refund" class="text-blue-600 cursor-pointer hover:underline font-semibold"></span>. 
            Contributions to open source projects are generally non-refundable.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
            <p class="text-red-800 font-semibold mb-2">ADMINISTRATIVE FEE CLAUSE:</p>
            <p class="text-red-700 text-sm">
              In case of refund, the processing fee charged by Stripe will be mandatorily deducted, 
              regardless of the reason for the refund, including payments made by mistake or user error. 
              This deduction is irrevocable and non-waivable, constituting an essential condition for service provision. 
              The refunded amount will always be the net amount after deduction of processing and administrative fees 
              incurred with the payment provider.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">5. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            You agree not to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 mb-6">
            <li>Use the site for illegal activities</li>
            <li>Attempt to bypass security measures</li>
            <li>Make fraudulent payments</li>
            <li>Interfere with site functionality</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            This site is provided "as is". We do not guarantee continuous availability or absence of errors. 
            Our liability is limited to the amount of payment made, <strong>respecting non-waivable 
            consumer rights</strong> under applicable legislation.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            The content of this site is protected by copyright. Open source projects maintain their 
            respective licenses.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">8. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            These terms are governed by Brazilian law. For international users, local consumer 
            protection and data privacy legislation also apply (GDPR, CCPA, PIPEDA, etc.). 
            Disputes will be resolved preferably through mediation or in the competent courts of Brazil.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">9. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For questions about these terms, contact us:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 mb-6">
            <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/evertramos" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">@evertramos</a></li>
            <li>Email: <span id="email-contact" class="text-blue-600 cursor-pointer hover:underline"></span></li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">10. Consumer Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            <strong>Nothing in these terms limits your rights as a consumer</strong> under 
            Consumer Defense Code (Brazil), GDPR (EU), CCPA (California) or similar legislation. 
            In case of conflict, consumer protection laws prevail.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">11. Changes</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            These terms may be updated at any time. <strong>Substantial changes</strong> 
            that affect your rights will be communicated with reasonable advance notice. 
            Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<script>
  // Build email dynamically to avoid bots
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    const user = 'evert.ramos';
    const domain = 'gmail.com';
    const email = user + '@' + domain;
    
    // Email for general contact
    const emailContactElement = document.getElementById('email-contact');
    if (emailContactElement) {
      emailContactElement.textContent = email;
      emailContactElement.onclick = function() {
        window.location.href = 'mailto:' + email;
      };
    }
    
    // Email for refunds
    const emailRefundElement = document.getElementById('email-refund');
    if (emailRefundElement) {
      emailRefundElement.textContent = email;
      emailRefundElement.onclick = function() {
        window.location.href = 'mailto:' + email + '?subject=Refund%20Request';
      };
    }
  });
</script>